---
// Custom Hero component for RTMX landing page
// Large hero illustration at top with closed-loop agent workflow
import TerminalCarousel from './TerminalCarousel.astro';
---

<!-- Hero Title at Very Top -->
<div class="hero-header">
  <h1 class="hero-title">The Intent Layer for Agentic Engineering</h1>
  <p class="hero-subtitle">
    The answer to AI building the wrong thing isn't better AI. It's better engineering discipline applied to AI.
    RTMX is the contract between human intent and AI agent execution — requirements, tests, and traceability integrated directly into the agentic engineering lifecycle.
  </p>
  <p class="hero-ucp">The only tool that gives AI agents a queryable, verifiable, dependency-aware requirements model that lives in git.</p>
  <div class="hero-buttons">
    <a href="https://github.com/rtmx-ai/rtmx-go" class="github-button" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor">
        <path d="M12 .297c-6.63 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.303 3.438 9.8 8.205 11.385.6.113.82-.258.82-.577 0-.285-.01-1.04-.015-2.04-3.338.724-4.042-1.61-4.042-1.61C4.422 18.07 3.633 17.7 3.633 17.7c-1.087-.744.084-.729.084-.729 1.205.084 1.838 1.236 1.838 1.236 1.07 1.835 2.809 1.305 3.495.998.108-.776.417-1.305.76-1.605-2.665-.3-5.466-1.332-5.466-5.93 0-1.31.465-2.38 1.235-3.22-.135-.303-.54-1.523.105-3.176 0 0 1.005-.322 3.3 1.23.96-.267 1.98-.399 3-.405 1.02.006 2.04.138 3 .405 2.28-1.552 3.285-1.23 3.285-1.23.645 1.653.24 2.873.12 3.176.765.84 1.23 1.91 1.23 3.22 0 4.61-2.805 5.625-5.475 5.92.42.36.81 1.096.81 2.22 0 1.606-.015 2.896-.015 3.286 0 .315.21.69.825.57C20.565 22.092 24 17.592 24 12.297c0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12"/>
      </svg>
      Star on GitHub
    </a>
    <a href="/installation" class="hero-button secondary">
      Try RTMX
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Full-width Hero Illustration -->
<section class="hero-illustration-section">
  <div class="hero-illustration-container">
    <img src="/hero-illustration.svg" alt="RTMX closed-loop workflow: AI Agent creates requirements, links to tests, reports status, agent queries via MCP" />
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Animated Terminal Carousel -->
<TerminalCarousel />

<!-- Collapse Your Stack Section -->
<section class="vision-section">
  <div class="vision-header">
    <span class="vision-label">The Shift</span>
    <h2>Collapse Your Stack for Agentic Engineering</h2>
  </div>

  <p class="vision-intro">
    Today you chat in Slack about what to build. Write a ticket in Jira describing what you chatted about.
    Write code in a repo that's supposed to implement the ticket. Message in Slack again when it's done.
    Most coordination overhead is just keeping these layers in sync with each other.
  </p>

  <div class="shift-grid not-content">
    <div class="shift-card">
      <div class="shift-icon">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/>
          <line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/>
          <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3>A Product Team in Your Laptop</h3>
      <p>Every engineer now has an entire product team inside their machine. The industry's capacity is massively scaling. The old coordination layer can't keep up.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="shift-card">
      <div class="shift-icon">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5z"/>
          <path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"/>
          <path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Collaborate Through the Artifact</h3>
      <p>Requirements, tests, status, and collaboration all live in the same structure, right next to the code. You don't chat about what to build — you look at the shared context and build.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="shift-card">
      <div class="shift-icon">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Zero-Trust by Design</h3>
      <p>Work across corporate lines without muddying network security policies. E2E encrypted, offline-first, air-gap ready. Your context stays yours.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="shift-card">
      <div class="shift-icon">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
          <path d="M2 12h20"/>
          <path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Flat and Wide</h3>
      <p>Not hierarchical teams behind ticket queues, but distributed engineers and their agents collaborating through a shared, decentralized protocol. The terminal is the team room.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<section class="feature-grid not-content">
  <a href="/guides/cli-reference" class="feature-card">
    <h3>One Command to See Everything</h3>
    <p>
      Know exactly where your project stands. <code>rtmx status</code> shows
      what's done, what's blocked, and what needs tests.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/guides/markers" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Proof, Not Promises</h3>
    <p>
      Every requirement links to a test that proves it works — across Python, Go, Java, TypeScript,
      and all major languages. Status comes from test results, not opinions.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/adapters/mcp" class="feature-card">
    <h3>AI That Knows Your Project</h3>
    <p>
      AI agents can query your requirements in real-time via MCP.
      They always know what to build next.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/adapters" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Works With Your Tools</h3>
    <p>
      Sync to GitHub Issues, Jira, or keep everything local in version control.
      Your data, your choice.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/guides/dependencies" class="feature-card">
    <h3>See What's Blocking You</h3>
    <p>
      Visualize dependencies and find the critical path to done.
      Stop guessing what to work on next.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/guides/schema" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Catch Mistakes Before They Ship</h3>
    <p>
      Validate requirements against your team's standards automatically.
      Extensible for aerospace, medical, and defense.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/pricing" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Your Data Stays Yours</h3>
    <p>
      No cloud required. Open source and auditable.
      Git-native audit trail for compliance.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/reference/architecture" class="feature-card">
    <h3>Programmable Requirements</h3>
    <p>
      Full API in Python and Go. Query, filter, and automate from any script or notebook.
      Build custom workflows.
    </p>
  </a>

  <a href="/pricing" class="feature-card coming-soon">
    <span class="badge">Coming Soon</span>
    <h3>Team Sync</h3>
    <p>
      CRDT-based collaboration with automatic conflict resolution.
      Multiple users, one source of truth.
    </p>
  </a>
</section>

<section class="comparison-section">
  <h2>Different Category, Not a Better Version</h2>
  <p class="comparison-subtitle">Spec authoring tools help AI write better code. Test frameworks execute scenarios. RTMX connects intent to code to proof across the full lifecycle.</p>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table class="comparison-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th></th>
          <th>Spec Authoring<span class="comparison-examples">OpenSpec, Kiro</span></th>
          <th>Test Execution<span class="comparison-examples">Cucumber, Gauge</span></th>
          <th>Task Trackers<span class="comparison-examples">Jira, Linear</span></th>
          <th class="rtmx-col">RTMX</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>When it helps</td>
          <td>Before code</td>
          <td>During testing</td>
          <td>Sprint planning</td>
          <td class="check">Full lifecycle</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>What it manages</td>
          <td>Change proposals</td>
          <td>Test scenarios</td>
          <td>Tasks & tickets</td>
          <td class="check">Requirements register + traceability</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Status source</td>
          <td>Human review</td>
          <td>Pass/fail per scenario</td>
          <td>Manual updates</td>
          <td class="check">Derived from linked tests</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Dependency graph</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="partial">Basic</td>
          <td class="check">Full graph + cycle detection</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>AI agent access</td>
          <td class="partial">Slash commands</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">API only</td>
          <td class="check">Native MCP server</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Cross-phase backlog</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="cross">No</td>
          <td class="partial">Board view</td>
          <td class="check">Dependency-aware</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Data lives in</td>
          <td>Markdown files</td>
          <td>Feature files</td>
          <td>Centralized SaaS</td>
          <td class="check">CSV in git</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Collaboration</td>
          <td>Local files</td>
          <td>SaaS add-on</td>
          <td>SaaS required</td>
          <td class="check">CRDT sync (decentralized)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="comparison-note">RTMX works <em>with</em> these tools, not against them. Use OpenSpec for spec authoring. Use Cucumber for BDD execution. RTMX is the traceability layer that sits above both.</p>
</section>

<!-- I Built RTMX Using RTMX Section -->
<section class="dogfood-section" id="dogfood">
  <div class="vision-header">
    <span class="vision-label">Dogfooding</span>
    <h2>I Built RTMX Using RTMX</h2>
  </div>

  <p class="dogfood-intro">
    RTMX isn't a theoretical tool. I use it every day to build RTMX itself — and to build
    an open-source radar system, hardware design tools, and other real products with agentic AI.
    The requirements traceability matrix for RTMX is managed by RTMX.
  </p>

  <div class="dogfood-grid not-content">
    <div class="dogfood-card">
      <span class="dogfood-stat">87</span>
      <span class="dogfood-label">requirements tracked</span>
      <p>Every feature, from CLI commands to CRDT sync, is a formal requirement with an ID, spec, and linked tests.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="dogfood-card">
      <span class="dogfood-stat">62%</span>
      <span class="dogfood-label">complete and verified</span>
      <p>Status is derived from test results, not opinions. When tests pass, requirements are complete. When they don't, I know exactly what's broken.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="dogfood-card">
      <span class="dogfood-stat">13</span>
      <span class="dogfood-label">development phases</span>
      <p>From foundation through CRDT sync and compliance — the full roadmap is a dependency graph, not a wish list.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="dogfood-card">
      <span class="dogfood-stat">0</span>
      <span class="dogfood-label">external dependencies for context</span>
      <p>No Jira. No Linear. No Slack channel for coordination. The requirements live in CSV, in git, next to the code. My agents read the backlog and build.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="dogfood-quote">
    Slow is smooth and smooth is fast. I spend hours — sometimes days — building and refining requirements
    and feature specifications before I start test-driven development. That time isn't wasted. It's the
    investment that makes everything downstream faster, more coherent, and more sustainable.
  </p>

  <div class="still-reading">
    <a href="/roadmap" class="hero-button secondary">See the Roadmap</a>
    <a href="/quickstart" class="hero-button primary">Get Started</a>
  </div>
</section>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <p>
    <a href="mailto:dev@rtmx.ai">dev@rtmx.ai</a>
  </p>
</footer>

<style is:global>
  /* Hide Starlight's default hero/title on homepage */
  .hero,
  main > header,
  .content-panel > header,
  [aria-label="Main"] > header,
  .main-pane > h1:first-child,
  .sl-markdown-content > h1:first-child {
    display: none !important;
  }

  /* Equal-height grid cards - global to avoid scoping specificity issues */
  .shift-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  }

  .shift-card {
    background: #171717;
    border: 1px solid #262626;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .shift-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .shift-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .dogfood-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  }

  .dogfood-card {
    background: #0d0d0d;
    border: 1px solid #1f1f1f;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .dogfood-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .dogfood-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>

<style>
  /* Hero Header - Title at very top */
  .hero-header {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 2rem 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0a0a0a 0%, #0f0f0f 100%);
  }

  .hero-title {
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #6ee7b7 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: #9ca3af;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    max-width: 850px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .hero-ucp {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #10b981;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 850px;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .hero-buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hero-button {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .hero-button.primary {
    background: #10b981;
    color: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .hero-button.primary:hover {
    background: #6ee7b7;
  }

  .hero-button.secondary {
    background: transparent;
    color: #10b981;
    border: 2px solid #10b981;
  }

  .hero-button.secondary:hover {
    background: #10b981;
    color: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .github-button {
    background: #10b981;
    color: #0a0a0a;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .github-button:hover {
    background: #6ee7b7;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.4);
  }

  /* Hero Illustration - Full width */
  .hero-illustration-section {
    width: 100%;
    background: #0f0f0f;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-illustration-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .hero-illustration-container img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  /* Feature Grid */
  .feature-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: #0f0f0f;
  }

  .feature-card {
    background: #171717;
    border: 1px solid #262626;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
  }

  .feature-card:hover {
    border-color: #10b981;
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .feature-card h3 {
    color: #f9fafb;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .feature-card p {
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .feature-card code {
    background: #262626;
    color: #e5e7eb;
    padding: 0.15em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 0.25rem;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  .feature-card.coming-soon {
    position: relative;
    border-color: #f59e0b40;
    justify-content: flex-start;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .feature-card.coming-soon h3,
  .feature-card.coming-soon p {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
  }

  .feature-card.coming-soon:hover {
    border-color: #f59e0b;
  }

  .feature-card .badge {
    position: absolute;
    top: -10px;
    right: 1rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f59e0b 0%, #d97706 100%);
    color: #0a0a0a;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* Comparison table extras */
  .comparison-examples {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #6b7280;
    text-transform: none;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .rtmx-col {
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.05);
  }

  .comparison-note {
    text-align: center;
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .comparison-note em {
    color: #10b981;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Comparison Section */
  .comparison-section {
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    background: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .comparison-section h2 {
    color: #f9fafb;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  .comparison-subtitle {
    color: #9ca3af;
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .comparison-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    background: #171717;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    overflow: hidden;
    table-layout: fixed;
  }

  .comparison-table th,
  .comparison-table td {
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #262626;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  .comparison-table th:first-child,
  .comparison-table td:first-child {
    text-align: left;
    width: 25%;
  }

  .comparison-table th:not(:first-child),
  .comparison-table td:not(:first-child) {
    width: 15%;
  }

  .comparison-table th {
    background: #0f0f0f;
    color: #f9fafb;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .comparison-table td {
    color: #d1d5db;
  }

  .comparison-table .check {
    color: #22c55e;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .comparison-table .cross {
    color: #6b7280;
  }

  .comparison-table .partial {
    color: #f59e0b;
  }

  .comparison-table .coming-soon {
    color: #f59e0b;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Footer */
  .site-footer {
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px solid #262626;
    background: #0a0a0a;
  }

  .site-footer p {
    color: #6b7280;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .site-footer a {
    color: #10b981;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .site-footer a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  /* "I Built RTMX Using RTMX" Section */
  .dogfood-section {
    background: #070707;
    padding: 4rem 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #262626;
  }

  .dogfood-intro {
    text-align: center;
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .dogfood-stat {
    display: block;
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #6ee7b7 100%);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .dogfood-label {
    display: block;
    color: #f9fafb;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .dogfood-card p {
    color: #9ca3af;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dogfood-quote {
    text-align: center;
    color: #d1d5db;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
